article.headline: IUPUI 79, Centenary 67
article.story: SHREVEPORT, La. -- Robert Glenn and Leroy Nobles scored 20 points apiece to lead Indiana University-Purdue University Indianapolis to a 79-67 win over Centenary on Thursday night. Alex Young added 18 points and nine rebounds for the Jaguars (14-11, 7-7 Summit Conference), who have won five of their last six games. Gary Redus II led the Gentlemen (7-18, 5-8) with 24 points and seven rebounds. Chase Adams chipped in 20 points and Nick Stallings had 10. IUPUI led by seven points at halftime, and outscored Centenary 41-36 in the second half to seal the win. The Jaguars went 7-for-12 from beyond the arc in the game, including a perfect 4-for-4 night for Nobles. Young was 2-for-4. The Gentlemen went just 7-for-22 from long range. IUPUI won the rebounding battle 31-24.
